Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech in Eastern Kentucky, highlighting the progress being made in combating opioid abuse and addiction. He praised Governor Matt Bevin for his work in cutting state red tape and creating more than 50,000 jobs. Pence also discussed the efforts being made to reduce the supply of drugs coming into the country and secure the southern border. He announced an additional $400 million in grants from the Department of Health and Human Services to fight the drug crisis nationwide, with nearly $10 million going to Kentucky. Pence expressed hope for the future and encouraged those struggling with addiction to seek help.